.:: Puzzle 2x4-Level-7-19::.
City: boston, new-york, liverpool, hannover
The people use 4 different means of transport: boat, motorbike, skateboard, trike
1. the person traveling to new-york is on the left or right of the person traveling to liverpool##3
2. the person driving the trike is on the left of the person traveling to liverpool##1
3. the person driving the motorbike is somewhere to the left of the person driving the boat##5
4. the person traveling to hannover is on the far left##1
5. the person driving the trike is not the person traveling to liverpool##6
6. the person driving the motorbike is somewhere between the person traveling to boston and the person traveling to liverpool##7

.:: Answer ::.
|               |   1    |      2      |     3     |   4    |
| City   | hannover | liverpool | new-york      | boston |
| Transport     | trike  | skateboard  | motorbike | boat   |

